law.text:
As used in KRS 304.20-410 to 304.20-450:
"Alarm" means horn, bell, siren or other sounding device which is audible at three hundred (300) feet;
"Electronic lock or keyless device" means an electronic coding device with more than ten thousand (10,000) combinations. The combination shall be entered through a keyboard or similar data entry device or by means of a remote control device;
"Passive" means an antitheft device or system which is activated automatically when the operator turns the ignition key to the off position; and
"Tubular" means a type of lock whose key is cylindrically shaped and which has at least fifty thousand (50,000) combinations.
